<!-- DESCRIPTION -->
<div class="pd-description">
    <p>
        Developed a Blind Spot Detection System to improve vehicle 
        safety by detecting objects or vehicles present in the driver's 
        blind area. The project used an ultrasonic sensor to continuously 
        monitor nearby obstacles and provide warning indications through 
        an LED and buzzer whenever an object entered the danger zone.
    </p>
    <p>
        Designed and implemented the circuit using components such as a 
        555 Timer IC, comparator, transistor, ultrasonic sensor, LED, 
        and buzzer. The system was tested through both simulation and 
        hardware implementation to analyze object detection range and 
        alert response.
    </p>
    <p>
        This project helped in gaining practical knowledge of sensor 
        interfacing, analog electronics, comparator circuits, timer 
        applications, and automotive safety systems.
    </p>
